
=================
Spring Security
=================

-> Security is very important for every web application.

-> To protect our application & application data we need to implement security logic.

-> Spring Security is one of the module of spring framework.

-> Spring Security concept we can use to secure our web applications / REST APIs / Microservices.

-> To implment security, we need to know about two concepts

		1) Authentication

		2) Authorization

-> Authentication means verifying who can login into our application (login check).

-> Authorization means verifying which user can access which functionality in the application (Role Based Access).


==============================
Working with Spring Security
==============================

-> To secure our spring boot application we need to add below starter in pom.xml file

<dependency>
	<groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
	<artifactId>spring-boot-starter-security</artifactId>
</dependency>

Note-1: When we add above dependency in pom.xml file then by default our application will be secured with "http basic authentication"

Note-2: It will generate random password to access our application. 

-> We need to use below credentials to access our application

				Username : user

				Password : <copy the pwd from console>

Note-1: When we access application from browser then it will display default login page for authentication.				

Note-2: To access secured REST API from postman, we need to set Authentiation values in POSTMAN to send the request.

				Auth : Basic Auth
			    Username : user
				Password : <copy-from-console>				

