========================
Microservices Security
========================

=> Each microservice should NOT manage users independently.

=> Authentication should be centralized (keep that logic in one microservice)

			Ex: AUTH-SERVICE

=> Authorization should be decentralized. That means role based access should be managed by every microservice on its own.

## API Gateway Level

.requestMatchers("/admin/**").hasRole("ADMIN")
.requestMatchers("/user/**").hasAnyRole("USER","ADMIN")

## Microservice Level

@PreAuthorize("hasRole('ADMIN')")
@GetMapping("/admin/data")
public String adminData() {
    return "Admin only data";
}

=> Services should communicate securely

=> No session state (stateless security)


